        "20002": {
            "id": "20002",
            "marks": 3,
            "negative_marks": 1.0,
            "is_input_type": false,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "Find the maximum value of (A + B + C) such that A, B, C are prime numbers and AB + BC + CA = 360. 1 &nbsp;",
            "options": [
                "",
                "",
                "",
                "Not possible"
            ],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "4"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution: <br>Correct Answer : <b>4</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div><b>As A, B, C are prime numbers, two cases arise either all\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tthree are odd number or one of them is 2 and other two\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tare odd\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tnumbers. In both the cases (AB + BC + CA) will be odd\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tand cannot be equal to 360, which is an even number.\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t</div></div>"
        },
