        "20005": {
            "id": "20005",
            "marks": 3,
            "negative_marks": 1.0,
            "is_input_type": false,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "A certain soft-drink is sold in a cylindrical can. The company reduced the diameter of the can by 10% but continued to fill the can of soft-drink to the same height as before. If the can of soft-drink is sold at the same price as before, what is the increase in profit percentage that the company will make per can? 1 &nbsp;",
            "options": [
                "%",
                "%",
                ".47%",
                "Cannot be determined"
            ],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "4"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<br>Correct Answer : <b>4</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div><b>The new cost price per can would be 81% of the old cost price (90% \u00d7\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t90%).\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tHowever, since we do not know the selling price, we cannot determine the\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tincrease in profit. Cannot be determined.</div></div>"
        },
        "20006": {
            "id": "20006",
            "marks": 3,
            "negative_marks": 0.0,
            "is_input_type": true,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "If f(x) = x<sup>2</sup> + 1 and g(x) = 2x \u2013 3 be two functions, then find value of f[g(f(g(f(x))))] + g[f(g(f(g(x))))] at x = 1. <ul class='list-group'> <li class='list-group-item'><B><a href='#quesSol1576269' data-toggle='collapse' aria-expanded='true'> Answer key/Solution</a></B> </li> </ul>",
            "options": [],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "3"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution:\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<br>Correct Answer : <b>3</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div><b>Firstly, f(g(f(g(f(x))))) at x = 1 is f(g(f(g(2)))), as f(1) = 2.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tNow as g(2) = 1, f(g(f(1))) = f(g(2)) = f(1) = 2.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tSimilarly, g(f(g(f(g(x))))) = 1.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tSo, the required result = 2 + 1 = 3</div></div>"
        },
