            "is_input_type": false,
            "is_multi_select": false,
            "instructions": "",
            "question_text": "Aroop leaves from Mumbai towards Goa, having a distance of 600 km, by his car. He travels at a speed of 50 km/hr for the first 6 hours and completes the remaining journey at a speed of 100 km/ hr. If he returns from Goa to Mumbai at an average speed of 80 km/hr, then time taken by him during the return journey is how much more/less than that of his journey from Mumbai to Goa? 1 &nbsp;",
            "options": [
                "hr more",
                ".5 hr more",
                ".5 hr less",
                "hr less"
            ],
            "correct_response": [
                [
                    "3"
                ]
            ],
            "solution": "<div><B>Solution: <br>Correct\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAnswer : <b>3</B>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t<div>Journey from Mumbai to Goa takes 9 hours.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tAs during first 6 hr at 50km/hr he covers 300km, and so the remaining 300 km at 100\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tkm/hr in 3hrs.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tHence total time taken = 9 hours.<br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tThe return journey at average speed of 80 km/hr takes 7.5 hours.<br><br>\n\t\t\t\t\t\t\t\tHence, the return journey takes 1.5 hr less.</div></div>"
        },
